# Plan: Add `image-text-to-text` Pipeline to Transformers.js

## Context

The codebase already supports `AutoModelForImageTextToText` in `src/models.js` (with backing model classes for LLaVa, Florence-2, Qwen2-VL, SmolVLM, PaliGemma, etc.) but there is no corresponding pipeline class in `src/pipelines.js`. This plan adds `ImageTextToTextPipeline`, which accepts an image + a text prompt, runs the model's `generate()`, and returns `[{ generated_text: string }]`.

The primary references are:
- **`ImageToTextPipeline`** (line 1975) – same output format, same processor/tokenizer/generate pattern
- **`DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline`** (line 2732) – same dual input (image + text), same `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs`

---

## Critical File

**`src/pipelines.js`** — the only file that needs changes.

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — Add import for `AutoModelForImageTextToText`

**Location:** Lines 20–45 (the `import { ... } from './models.js'` block).

Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the existing destructured import list, after `AutoModelForDocumentQuestionAnswering` (line 40):

```js
import {
    // ... existing imports ...
    AutoModelForDocumentQuestionAnswering,
    AutoModelForImageTextToText,   // ← ADD THIS LINE
    AutoModelForImageToImage,
    // ... rest ...
} from './models.js';
```

---

### Step 2 — Add JSDoc typedefs and class (after `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline`, ~line 2780)

Insert the following block after the closing `}` of `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` (line 2779) and before the blank line / `TextToAudioPipeline` block (~line 2782):

```js
/**
 * @typedef {Object} ImageTextToTextSingle
 * @property {string} generated_text The generated text.
 * @typedef {ImageTextToTextSingle[]} ImageTextToTextOutput
 *
 * @callback ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback Generate text based on an image and a text prompt.
 * @param {ImageInput} image The image to be processed.
 * @param {string} text The text prompt describing what to do with the image.
 * @param {Partial<import('./generation/configuration_utils.js').GenerationConfig>} [options] Additional keyword arguments to pass along to the generate method of the model.
 * @returns {Promise<ImageTextToTextOutput>} An array of objects containing the generated text(s).
 *
 * @typedef {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs & ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback & Disposable} ImageTextToTextPipelineType
 */

/**
 * Image-Text-To-Text pipeline using any `AutoModelForImageTextToText`. This pipeline accepts
 * an image and a text prompt, and generates text based on both inputs.
 *
 * **Example:** Describe an image with `onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft`.
 * ```javascript
 * const pipe = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft');
 * const url = 'https://huggingface.co/datasets/Xenova/transformers.js-docs/resolve/main/cats.jpg';
 * const output = await pipe(url, 'Describe this image in detail');
 * // [{ generated_text: 'Two cats are lying on a couch.' }]
 * ```
 */
export class ImageTextToTextPipeline extends (/** @type {new (options: TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs) => ImageTextToTextPipelineType} */ (Pipeline)) {

    /**
     * Create a new ImageTextToTextPipeline.
     * @param {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs} options An object used to instantiate the pipeline.
     */
    constructor(options) {
        super(options);
    }

    /** @type {ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback} */
    async _call(image, text, generate_kwargs = {}) {

        // Preprocess image
        const preparedImage = (await prepareImages(image))[0];
        const { pixel_values } = await this.processor(preparedImage);

        // Tokenize text prompt
        const { input_ids } = this.tokenizer(text, {
            padding: true,
            truncation: true,
        });

        // Run model generation with both pixel values and input IDs
        const output = await this.model.generate({
            inputs: input_ids,
            pixel_values,
            ...generate_kwargs,
        });

        // Decode generated token IDs back to text
        const decoded = this.tokenizer.batch_decode(/** @type {Tensor} */(output), {
            skip_special_tokens: true,
        }).map(x => ({ generated_text: x.trim() }));

        return decoded;
    }
}
```

**Reused utilities (already in file scope):**
- `prepareImages` — same helper used by `ImageToTextPipeline` and `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline`
- `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` typedef (line 215) — already defined, covers `{ model, tokenizer, processor, task }`

---

### Step 3 — Register in `SUPPORTED_TASKS`

**Location:** After the `"document-question-answering"` entry (ends ~line 3341), before `"image-to-image"`:

```js
"image-text-to-text": {
    "tokenizer": AutoTokenizer,
    "pipeline": ImageTextToTextPipeline,
    "model": AutoModelForImageTextToText,
    "processor": AutoProcessor,
    "default": {
        "model": "onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft",
    },
    "type": "multimodal",
},
```

---

### Step 4 — Add to pipeline factory JSDoc

**Location:** Lines 3418–3440 (the `@param {T} task` bullet list inside the `pipeline()` JSDoc).

Add one line (alphabetically/logically fits between `"image-classification"` and `"image-segmentation"`, or at end of list):

```
 *  - `"image-text-to-text"`: will return a `ImageTextToTextPipeline`.
```

Insert after the `"image-to-text"` line (line 3427):
```
 *  - `"image-to-text"`: will return a `ImageToTextPipeline`.
 *  - `"image-text-to-text"`: will return a `ImageTextToTextPipeline`.   ← ADD
